2500|$|Southern Baptists observe two ordinances: the Lord's Supper and believer's baptism (also {{known as}} credo-baptism, from the Latin for [...] "I believe"). Furthermore, they hold the {{historic}} Baptist belief that immersion {{is the only}} valid mode of baptism. <b>The</b> Baptist <b>Faith</b> and Message describes baptism as a symbolic act of obedience and a testimony of <b>the</b> believer's <b>faith</b> <b>in</b> <b>Jesus</b> Christ. <b>The</b> BF also notes that baptism is a precondition to church membership.|$|R
